@startuml Demo Run Saved Report
title Demo Flow: Run Saved Report from Library

actor "Demo User" as User
participant "AlpineJS (Frontend)" as UI
participant "ReportBuilderController" as Controller
participant "DynamicReport (Facade)" as Engine

User -> UI : Click "Run" on a Report in Library
activate UI
UI -> Controller : POST /builder/saved/{id}/execute
activate Controller

Controller -> Engine : loadAndGenerate(id)
activate Engine
Engine -> Engine : Fetch SavedReport from DB
Engine -> Engine : Parse JSON Payload to AST
Engine -> Engine : generate(AST)\n(Apply BFS Joins, VAs, Filters, Sorts)
Engine --> Controller : Laravel Query Builder
deactivate Engine

Controller -> Controller : builder->paginate(50)
Controller -> Controller : builder->toSql()
Controller -> Engine : explainJoinPlan(ReportRequest)
Controller --> UI : JSON Response\n{success: true, sql: "...", join_plan: [...], results: [...], pagination: {...}}
deactivate Controller

UI -> UI : Render SQL footprint\nRender Data Table
note right of UI: Notice that visual configuration blocks\nare bypassed entirely.
UI --> User : Display Results
deactivate UI

@enduml
